        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Translate_Adapter::[translate,isTranslated]() don't return the expected result.\n\nScenery:\n\nfile.tmx\n{quote}\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE tmx SYSTEM \"tmx14.dtd\">\n<tmx version=\"1.4\">\n<header\/>\n<body>\n    <tu tuid='Message_Error_1'><tuv xml:lang=\"en_US\"><seg>ERROR-1<\/seg><\/tuv><\/tu>\n    <tu tuid='Message_Error_2'><tuv xml:lang=\"en\"><seg>ERROR-2<\/seg><\/tuv><\/tu>\n<\/body>\n<\/tmx>\n{quote}\n\n{code}\n$lang = new Zend_Translate('tmx', 'file.tmx', 'en_US') ;\nvar_dump($lang->getList()) ;\nvar_dump($lang->getLocale()) ;\n{code}\n\nWell, this return respectively \"array('en_US'=>'en_US','en'=>'en')\" and string \"string('en_US')\".\n\nNow, what happens if I do this?\n{code}\n$lang->isTranslated('Message_Error_2',true) ;\n{code}\nThis return \"bool(false)\". NO OBJECTION.\n\nBut if I do this?\n{code}\n$lang->isTranslated('Message_Error_2',false) ;\n{code}\nThis sholud return \"bool(true)\", instead \"bool(false)\" is returned. THIS IS BAD.\n\nThis error is due to a wrong if check in translate() and isTranslated() code.\n\nDiff in attachment."
        },
