                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15526",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You're right... this is not the expected behaviour.\n\nFixed with SVN 5464... thnx for your help",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-27T15:04:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-27T15:04:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15527",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=d.orlando.0",
                        "name": "d.orlando.0",
                        "displayName": "Daniele Orlando",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks to you, Thomas.\nBut SVN 5464 doesn't fix the issue of Zend_Translate_Adapter::translate(), that is identica,l but only Zend_Translate_Adapter::isTranslated().\n\nI have one question: Why Zend_Translate_Adapter name doesn't follow the zend coding standard? Its name should be Zend_Translate_Adapter_Abstract. Is it correct? Maybe an issue?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=d.orlando.0",
                        "name": "d.orlando.0",
                        "displayName": "Daniele Orlando",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-27T16:33:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-27T16:33:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15530",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No...\nThe class name is Zend_Translate_Adapter... abstract is only the type of class not the name...\nThe naming follows the coding standard.\n\nThis naming scheme is also used by Zend_Memory or Zend_Pdf for example.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-27T17:08:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-27T17:08:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15546",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=d.orlando.0",
                        "name": "d.orlando.0",
                        "displayName": "Daniele Orlando",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, Zend_Memory and Zend_Pdf have not the abstract suffix but this is not a valid reson to consider this way a good way.\n\nPlease, try this test:\n\nWhat do you think \"Zend_Pdf_Element\" is?\nAbstract.\n\nAnd what about \"Zend_Pdf_FileParser\"?\nAbstract too.\n\nAnd \"Zend_Pdf_Page\"?\nClass.\n\nAnd \"Zend_Pdf_Parser\"?\nClass too.\n\nAnd \"Zend_Pdf_Font\"?\nAbstract again.\n\nAnd \"Zend_Pdf_Style\"?\nClass again.\n\nAnd \"Zend_Pdf_Filter\"?\n...\nINTERFACE.\n\n;)\n\nWhat a mess.\nThis is not a good convention. I see no convention here.\n\nZend_Pdf_Element_Abstract\nZend_Pdf_Filter_Interface \nZend_Pdf_Page\ncan be considered a convention, a good convention.\n\nThe situation is just a bit better with Zend_Memory.\nZend_Memory_Container_Interface is an Interface\nVERY WELL!\nZend_Memory_Container is an Abstract class\nARGHHH!\n\nZend_Db_Table was an abstract class and is deprecated since 0.9. Now its name is Zend_Db_Table_Abstract.\nAnother example of good implementation is the abstract class Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract.\nZend_Db_Table_Abstract, Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract, Zend_Translate_Adapter are all \"Adapter pattern\" implementation. Why a different name convention?\n\nI know we are near the 1.0.GA but we can't have a bad name convention that became unchangeble throughout the 1.* release. The change of name is hidden to the user and there is no break of compatibility with old revision.\nThis is the moment to fix it. There is no reason to have this bad nomenclature.\nWe aren't discussing if Zend_Translate has to change in Zend_Translator, but what should be the name of all Abstract class and Interface.\nThis is not a stupid cavil, but a matter of clearness.\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV\/Contributing+to+Zend+Framework\n{quote}\n\"All framework code is covered by the PHP Coding Standard (draft). Learn it, love it, live it.\". \n{quote}\nYes, but I want a good standard.\n\nReferences:\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV\/PHP+Coding+Standard+%28draft%29\n{quote}\nInterfaces\n\nInterface classes must follow the same conventions as other classes (see above), but must end with \"_Interface\", such as in these examples:\nZend_Log_Adapter_Interface \nZend_Controller_Dispatcher_Interface \n{quote}\n \nAnd what about abstract class?\nI can instance a class and for this reason we have no suffix.\nI can't instance an interface and for this reason we have the \"_Interface\" suffix.\nI can't instance an abstract class and for this reason we should have the \"_Abstract\" suffix.\nI think that ZendCodingStandard(DRAFT) lacks in this point.\n\nZend_Pdf_Filter is an interface and its name is wrong. This is not a reason to imitate it. Or not?\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-1228.\nThomas, this issue is your. Why have you renamed Zend_Feed_EntryAbstract in Zend_Feed_Entry_Abstract and not in Zend_Feed_Entry?\nI think you have done the right thing. Why not with Zend_Translate_Adapter?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=d.orlando.0",
                        "name": "d.orlando.0",
                        "displayName": "Daniele Orlando",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-28T09:34:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-28T09:34:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15555",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Daniele, I am not the one you must persuade ;-)\n\nThe standard is made by Zend's dev team. Also the issue you mentioned is not my idea... I only did the coding because no one felt to be owner of this one.\n\nAnd as last thing to mention:\nFor changing such an ammount of class names it's almost too late. We are 2 weeks before 1.0. Such a change can not be done because of the API freeze. We're actually only bug fixing.\n\nBtw:\nEven if I wish to change the naming I am not allowed without the devteam to be aware of it.\n\nAnyway... this ticket is not the right place for such a discussion.\nEach ticket should only contain the things related to it self. And this ticket is related to a TMX problem (which is already solved).\n\nI would suggest that you \"create an issue with all classes which have the wrong naming scheme\"\nYou suggest to change \/ adopt the coding standard.\nMail to the dev team about this one.\nMail to the mailing list for getting others aware of this.\nWhen we change such things they should be done consistent for all classes within the framework not only for one class... ZF1228 was also not the only one related to naming scheme.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-28T12:17:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-28T12:17:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15558",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=d.orlando.0",
                        "name": "d.orlando.0",
                        "displayName": "Daniele Orlando",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm sorry, You are right.\n\nForgive me for the nuissance...I'm new of the community.\n\nAnyway, thanks for the tip. I'll follow your suggestion.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=d.orlando.0",
